-- Wind Venture Funding Rises in Third Quarter, Mercom Capital Says
-- B y   A n d r e w   H e r n d o n
-- 2012-10-23T19:45:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-23/wind-venture-funding-rises-in-third-quarter-mercom-capital-says.html
Venture capital investment in wind
energy more than tripled during the third quarter while the
acquisitions fell, according to Mercom Capital Group LLC.  Venture capital companies completed six financing deals
worth a total of $57 million in the quarter, up from three deals
worth $17 million in the second quarter, the Austin, Texas-based
communications company said today in an e-mailed statement.  There were 11 acquisitions in the wind industry valued at
$53 million, compared to five deals worth $93 million in the
prior quarter, Mercom said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Herndon in San Francisco at 
